  "updateinfo_id": "ALSA-2026:3477",
  "description": "The gnutls packages provide the GNU Transport Layer Security (GnuTLS) library, which implements cryptographic algorithms and protocols such as SSL, TLS, and DTLS.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * gnutls: Stack-based Buffer Overflow in gnutls_pkcs11_token_init() Function (CVE-2025-9820)\n  * gnutls: GnuTLS: Denial of Service via excessive resource consumption during certificate verification (CVE-2025-14831)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
